(## 6. System Architecture) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(### High-level architecture explanation) Tj
0 -14 Td
(MockMind follows a classic SPA + API architecture:) Tj
0 -14 Td
(1. React SPA handles UI, local state, and authenticated API calls.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(2. Express API orchestrates business logic, auth, validation, and third-party integrations.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(3. MongoDB stores users, sessions, feedback/contact records, and admin account.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(4. GridFS stores uploaded answer audio files.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(5. Groq provides AI-powered runtime features.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(### Client-server interaction) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Client sends REST requests with JWT bearer token.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Backend middleware validates token and hydrates `req.user` / `req.admin`.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Controllers validate payloads, execute domain logic, and return JSON responses.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(### Data flow) Tj
0 -14 Td
(1. User configures practice session in UI.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(2. Backend generates questions via Groq.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(3. User submits theory voice/coding text answers.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(4. Voice file is transcribed and audio persisted in GridFS.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(5. Final submission is evaluated by Groq and stored as `PracticeSession`.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(6. History and admin dashboards query persisted session and feedback/contact data.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(---) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
